# Agent rules

Read and follow `docs/rules.md` before significant work. That file is the source of truth; do not contradict it.

Apply it when planning, coding, debugging, adding dependencies, writing tests, or editing nodes and workflows.

## Sections (read the full doc for detail)

1. **Read before you write** ‚Äî inspect target files and existing patterns first.
2. **Think before you code** ‚Äî state assumptions and tradeoffs; ask when unclear.
3. **Simplicity** ‚Äî minimum code for the current problem; no premature abstraction.
4. **Surgical changes** ‚Äî smallest justified diff; match existing style.
5. **Verifications** ‚Äî prove fixes with failing tests; test real behavior.
6. **Goal-driven execution** ‚Äî define success criteria and plan multi-step work first.
7. **Debugging** ‚Äî reproduce, read errors fully, change one thing at a time.
8. **Dependencies** ‚Äî prefer stdlib/existing code; justify new packages.
9. **Communication** ‚Äî explain what and why; flag uncertainty precisely.
10. **Common failure modes** ‚Äî stop if you drift into kitchen-sink refactors or wrong abstractions.
11. **Node structure** ‚Äî workflows from root nodes only; graph traversal reads node data; use node templates; confirm template changes with the user.
12. **User-facing prompts** ‚Äî planner owns navigation (what to ask); `engine/messaging/` owns prompt copy (how to phrase it). Resolve via `build_parameter_input_prompt()`; defaults in `workflow_parameter_prompts.py`. Do not add prompt strings to `engine/planner/`.
13. **Graph-driven workflow paths** ‚Äî no hardcoded branches, steps, or parameter lists in engine/API/UI; paths from node expansion, assumptions, and edge `when` clauses. Replan after each input. See `docs/rules.md` ¬ß13 and `.cursor/rules/graph-expansion.mdc`.
14. **Parameter key consistency** ‚Äî lookup `inputs[].id`, fact keys, and workflow lists match `PARAM-*` `key`; see `docs/rules.md` ¬ß14 and `.cursor/rules/parameter-key-consistency.mdc`.
15. **Derived parameter value display** ‚Äî unresolved values produced by equations or lookups show a `value_reference` link in equation input tables, not "Awaiting user input"; see `docs/rules.md` ¬ß15.
16. **Lookup-derived parameters** ‚Äî table lookup outputs (E, W, Y, S, ‚Ä¶) are resolved from lookup keys via graph `returns_parameter` edges; do not ask users to confirm invented defaults; see `docs/rules.md` ¬ß16.
17. **PARAM-driven composer metadata** ‚Äî every gatherable parameter needs a `PARAM-*` node; composer label/type/units/options come from node metadata only (no engine fallbacks); see `docs/rules.md` ¬ß17 and `.cursor/rules/param-composer-metadata.mdc`.
18. **Lookup conditionals** ‚Äî table boundary/clamp rules on output `PARAM-*` nodes via `lookup_conditionals`; generic interpreter in `engine/graph/lookup_conditionals.py` only; see `docs/rules.md` ¬ß18 and `.cursor/rules/lookup-conditionals.mdc`.
19. **Planner traversal debug state** ‚Äî `PlannerTraversalState` on `EngineeringPlan` for inspector debugging; derived in `planner_traversal.py`; does not drive paths; inspector reads `engineering_plan`; see `docs/rules.md` ¬ß19.
20. **Engineering plan validation** ‚Äî `validate_engineering_plan()` invariants on normalized plan output; rejects flat `GOAL-*`/`REQ-*` maps; see `docs/rules.md` ¬ß20.
21. **Flow Guidance Layer** ‚Äî traversal narration in `presentation/guidance/workflows/` via `GuidanceResolver`; `ResponseComposer` merges guidance with `engine/messaging/` prompts; `presentation_blocks` owned by `PresentationResponse` (not workflow state); `transcript_blocks` append-only display history; see `docs/rules.md` ¬ß21.
22. **Plan Review Gate** ‚Äî every feature plan must include a **Plan Review Gate** section after Architecture Consistency Review; status APPROVED / REVISE / BLOCKED; write for non-technical reviewers; do not implement until APPROVED; see `docs/process/plan_review_gate.md`, `.cursor/rules/plan-review-gate.mdc`, `.cursor/rules/feature-planning.mdc`.
23. **Architecture Consistency Review** ‚Äî every feature plan must include an **Architecture Consistency Review** before the Plan Review Gate; status CLEAR / NEEDS_DOC_UPDATE / NEEDS_DECISION / BLOCKED; surfaces doc/architecture conflicts in plain English; see `docs/rules.md` ¬ß23.

For node, standards, or workflow work, re-read **¬ß11**, **¬ß13**, **¬ß14**, and **¬ß18** in `docs/rules.md` before editing.

For parameter asks, material autocomplete, or workflow composer copy, re-read **¬ß12** and **¬ß17** in `docs/rules.md` before editing.

For traversal narration and CLI transcript blocks, re-read **¬ß21** in `docs/rules.md` before editing.

For feature plans and non-trivial changes, include the **Architecture Consistency Review** (¬ß23) and **Plan Review Gate** (¬ß22) per `.cursor/rules/plan-review-gate.mdc` before writing production code.
